column27: The average age of the dogs in our rescue was 9 1/2, with 23 of the 30 dogs being 8 or older. and of those 23, fourteen were over the age of 10.  Our length of stay is much longer due to the number of seniors we take in.
One Adult dog that was taken in as a euthanasia request, died prior to euthanasia.

The average length of stay for adults was 29.75 days. This included a number of dogs with exceptionally long stays due to being in hospice or lengthy medical care for heartworm disease or other issues.

The median stay, that is LOS in the middle (half above and half below) rather than the average which is skewed by outlier values, for our dogs in 2016 was 15.5 days.

Our euthanasia number was higher this year due to taking in more senior dogs and having some of our hospice dogs pass away.

column115:
Birds are here for their lifetimes, so I put 356 days x ten years as the average LOS. Parrots, even small ones, can live decade, but finches and canaries have short lives (6 of the 10 deceased were canaries and finches). 

Adoptions are infrequent because: 1)I took down my website and my Facebook page a few years ago, so people only hear about Flitesong by word-of mouth; 2)  I put potential adopters through a rigorous screening process and most people are not willing to answer all my questions, so I don't adopt out to them; and 3) most of the birds here are very old of little interest to those wanting a pet bird. 

I purchased one zebra finch and my husband gave me a pair of diamond doves - all from PetsMart in Colorado Springs. Not sure how to show those commercially acquired birds on this form, so I put them under owner relinquished.
